<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">OOW tradeskill augs:
<br />
Dot shielding (Sphalerite) = % reduction in damage from dots
<br />
Spell shielding (Celestine) = % reduction in damage from spells
<br />
Stun resist (Apatite) = % chance to 'resist' a stun
<br />
Strikethrough (Howlite) = % chance to ignore a mob's dodge, block, parry on a hit
<br />

<br />
Stuff there's no oow tradesill aug for
<br />
Shielding  = % reduction in the damage bonus of a mob's melee
<br />
Avoidance = increased chance to avoid melee.  Not known exactly how it works.
<br />
Combat Effects = increased chance for a weapon to proc.
<br />
Accuracy = increased chance to hit.
<br />

<br />
Of the secondary effects that can be added, the only ones i've seen that were useful were improved dodge III and faerune.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
