<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">They 'work' exactly as advertised.  If an AE does 1000 damage, 1% spell shield will reduce it to 990 damage.  35% spell shield (which is the cap) will reduce it to 650 damage.  It definitely adds up if you eat a lot of AEs and in particular if the AEs you eat tend to be unresistable.  Whether or not its better than other augs is definitely dependent on where you are gearwise.  For me, resists are largely irelevant since bardsong is so ridiculously overpowered it doesn't matter much what i do gearwise, the only thing thats relevant is whether i have ae song or pov.  HP augs are of course always nice, but if you find a nice supply of them please fill us in on where <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" />  I've seen a total of 0 in the bazaar in months of checking it and have seen one total kyanite drop.
<br />

<br />
For augs, my preferences would be hp > stunresist > spellshield > dotshield >> resists.  Resist augs are basically free whereas the other augs cost a bit.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
